column10:
TL;DR Wanna milk an Old Dead Lady?

Wot I liked
- Loads of monsters of various types;
- Semi-random progression as you unlock more containment rooms each day;
- Managing an underground facility milking monsters for electricity!

Wot I disliked
- Very basic, almost non-existant controls;
- You can't choose room positioning;
- If you restart the game you have to redo successful days all the time;
- I didn't enjoy the repetitive nature of the game and the inability to affect the outcomes of anything;
- There's very little point in RTS-style approach.

To sum it all up, I've picked this game as it reminded me the cabin in the woods. I've expected a bit more Dungeon Keeper experience. The idea is very cool but the game is kinda grating.
